                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>good <add>ושובו מדרכיהם הרעים</add>; but when Teachers rise up, and by<lb/> precept\n                and example inculcate as unimportant, useless, and<lb/> contrary to the spirit of\n                the age — all or much of what they had<lb/> been trained up to observe — what is to\n                be expected? The awakened<lb/> religious feelings become enlisted in favor of what\n                requires so little<lb/> effort; only build a magnificent place of worship,\n                modernize,<lb/> hope<add>?</add> &amp; render agreeable its services, preserve\n                decorum, &amp; have an<lb/> external varnish of piety, and the <add>ר\"ה</add> is\n                attained. I place<lb/> a great deal of the blame for this wretched state of\n                affairs<lb/> on the shoulders of our so-called Orthodox chiefs, who are idle\n                &amp;<lb/> selfish, and contribute nothing to the <hi rend=\"underline\">general</hi>\n                good of <placeName>Israel</placeName>. All<lb/> their efforts seem concentrated on\n                little aims which began in their<lb/> own Synagogues and end there. And then there\n                is no unity of<lb/> action. Look for assistance at the several large congregations\n                at<lb/> the <placeName>North</placeName>. At the <placeName>19th St.</placeName>\n                Synagogue, everything seems to have been<lb/> attained in <persName>Mr\n                        Lyn's<add>?</add></persName> cadences &amp; his choir's artistic\n                performances.<lb/> The pulpit is silent, and does not seem to be needed. Our<lb/>\n                worthy brethren there are apparently contented with the order of<lb/> things as they\n                are, and are either so pious as not to require<lb/> explanations or so wicked as to\n                fear denunciation. At <persName>Dr. Raphall's</persName><lb/> &amp; <persName>Mr.\n                    Isaacs's</persName>, I hear trumpet-tongued praises of the <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >choir</hi>, in<lb/> the former, it is said, led by a Xian! Do you not remember\n                my<lb/> fickle and unsuccessful effort in <add>?</add> at the first Sephim of<lb/>\n                the Board of Delegates to have its scope of a character which</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3542k15k/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
