                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3542k15k/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>not depending on any Congregational action. I wish a few others<lb/> would attempt\n                the same procedure. I can but <hi rend=\"underline\">hope</hi> it.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Mr. Aletrino</persName> has shown some diligence<lb/> in\n                the matter of the Agency, and has handed me the following bit of<lb/> additional\n                subscribers, to whom please mail the Occident,—if possible<lb/> from the\n                    <date>Nissan</date> No. when the present Vol. began. If you cannot do this<lb/>\n                to all, endeavor to do so for the <persName>Messrs. De\n                    Meza</persName>.—<persName>Joshua D Henriques</persName>,<lb/>\n                <persName>E. de Pina</persName>, <persName>Morris Woolf</persName>, <persName>A de\n                    Sola</persName>, <persName>J. O. DeCastro</persName>, <persName>S J de\n                    Meza</persName>,<lb/>\n                <persName>A H de Meza</persName>, &amp; <persName>Henry Aaron</persName>.\n                    <persName>Mr B Y Benyamin</persName> is still uncertain<lb/> as to subscribing.\n                Send a list of amts due you by previous Sub.<lb/> for collection. Send the follg\n                Books p Express—addressed to <persName>Mr<lb/> M Alentino</persName>, <placeName>80\n                    Prytania St. - N.O.</placeName></p>\n            <table cols=\"2\" rows=\"4\">\n                <row>\n                    <cell>1 Set P Books — Sheep</cell>\n                    <cell>@ $25.00</cell>\n                </row>\n                <row>\n                    <cell>1 “ “ fancy</cell>\n                    <cell>@ $30.00</cell>\n                </row>\n                <row>\n                    <cell>1 Pentateuch Sheep mention the price</cell>\n                    <cell/>\n                </row>\n                <row>\n                    <cell>1 Bible Ea 3.50 &amp; 5.00</cell>\n                    <cell/>\n                </row>\n            </table>\n            <p>As soon as he collects for these and subsns. I will see that the amt.<lb/> be\n                promptly remitted you.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I hinted to <persName>Mr. Gutheim</persName> of his long\n                silence;<lb/> and I understood him to say he would soon write you. Perhaps he<lb/>\n                has already done so. The <placeName>Rampart St.</placeName> synagogue is to be torn\n                down &amp;<lb/> made more spacious, the adjoining lot having been purchased. The\n                Polish<lb/> on Colonial <add>?</add> to be finished for <add>פסח</add>, that on\n                    <placeName>Jackson St</placeName> for <add>Hebrew</add></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Mrs. Jacobs</persName> joins me in kind regards.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">Yours truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Henry S. Jacobs</persName>\n            </p>\n            <div>\n                <p>\n                    <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_24_3.pdf\">The above text refers to Occident\n                        Volume 24 No. 3 pages 97 through 106. Click here to view.</ref>\n                </p>\n            </div>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
